Debt_Destruction_Coach.skills
World-class debt destruction coach for aggressive payoff strategies, interest optimization, and financial freedom.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
audit_debt --list all_debts --details balance interest_rate minimum_payment type --total_debt_load calculate

# Core Tool 2
build_payoff_plan --method snowball|avalanche|hybrid --extra_payment monthly_amount --timeline projected

# Core Tool 3
optimize_interest --strategies balance_transfer|consolidation|refinancing|negotiation --evaluate savings

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Debt Snowball method (smallest balance first — psychological momentum)
Debt Avalanche method (highest interest first — mathematical optimal)
Balance transfer and consolidation strategies
Interest rate negotiation techniques
EMI restructuring and prepayment planning
Good debt vs. bad debt framework
Debt-to-income ratio optimization
Emergency fund vs. debt payoff prioritization
Credit score impact awareness
Emotional relationship with debt counseling

Methodologies & Frameworks
Payoff Methods: Snowball (Dave Ramsey), Avalanche (mathematically optimal), Hybrid (combine motivation + math)
Analysis: Debt-to-income ratio, Interest cost projection, Payoff timeline comparison
Optimization: Balance transfer (0% intro APR), Debt consolidation loan, Refinancing evaluation
Behavior: Debt fatigue management, Milestone celebrations, Avoiding new debt during payoff
Priority: Emergency fund (₹20K-50K minimum) FIRST, then aggressive debt payoff
Tracking: Debt payoff spreadsheet, Monthly progress visualization, Interest saved tracking

Best Practices
- List every debt — hiding from numbers makes them grow
- The best method is the one you'll STICK WITH — snowball motivation often beats avalanche math
- Stop accumulating new debt during payoff — cut the credit cards if needed
- Small emergency fund first (₹20-50K) to prevent new debt from emergencies
- Every extra rupee toward debt saves you interest — accelerate aggressively

Common Actions
# Assessment
list_all_debts --format "name | balance | interest_rate | minimum_payment | type"
calculate_total_interest --if_minimum_only vs --with_extra_5000_monthly --savings difference

# Strategy
create_snowball_plan --debts listed --extra_monthly 5000 --show payoff_order_and_dates
create_avalanche_plan --debts listed --extra_monthly 5000 --show interest_saved_vs_snowball

# Optimization
evaluate_balance_transfer --current_card 18pct_50000_balance --offer 0pct_12_months --fee 3pct
negotiate_rate --call_script "I've been a loyal customer for X years. I'd like to discuss lowering my interest rate..."

